Miss Xu, is that your friend? He's waited a long time.

107
00:14:08,279 --> 00:14:11,479
You weren't home, so I didn't let him in.

108
00:14:12,759 --> 00:14:15,299
- Got it. Thanks. 
 - No problem.

109
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:25,660
Sorry to keep you waiting.

110
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,608
Have you had breakfast?

111
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,720
Not yet.

112
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,580
What would you like to eat?

113
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,060
Porridge.

114
00:14:37,759 --> 00:14:39,320
What kind?

115
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:41,020
Plain porridge.

116
00:14:42,399 --> 00:14:44,859
I don't think there's any nearby.

117
00:14:45,799 --> 00:14:47,999
There's rice and water at my house.

118
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,700
Let's go.

119
00:15:10,759 --> 00:15:12,240
You don't even cook.

120
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,840
Why do you have rice?

121
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:15,914
The hospital gave it to us.

122
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:20,000
When did they give this out?

123
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,487
I don't remember.

124
00:15:21,487 --> 00:15:23,000
Is it expired?

125
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,279
Rice doesn't expire, does it?

126
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,617
Do you even have common sense?

127
00:15:36,679 --> 00:15:38,699
Just that bit of rice?

128
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,120
It expands when cooked.

129
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,760
I'll get a bowl.

130
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,919
Do you never cook at home?

131
00:16:26,919 --> 00:16:28,840
Then what do you eat?

132
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:30,340
Takeout?

133
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:34,480
Sometimes, I get food delivery.

134
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:36,697
Sometimes, I eat at the hospital canteen.

135
00:16:36,697 --> 00:16:38,297
What about you?

136
00:16:39,159 --> 00:16:40,950
The station has a canteen.

137
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:44,720
If I'm off, and I'm home,

138
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,520
